    "Balanced and diverse dataset curation: to address modalityspecific biases, it is essential to ensure that each dataset used in the training process is representative and balanced across demographic factors such as race, age, gender, and cultural background.",
    "This is especially important for multimodal learning, where biases from one modality can influence another, leading to unfair outcomes in applications.",
    "To prevent this, rigorous dataset curation is necessary.",
    "Data augmentation and synthetic data generation can be used to supplement underrepresented categories and enhance model robustness.",
    "Pouthier (2024) suggests this approach. 2."
  ],
